Brian T. Meyers Lawyer Kansas City, MO, KS Defective products injure thousands of people across the U.S. each year. From burns to broken bones, amputations and electrocutions, dangerous appliances, tools and machines can cause severe injuries to the consumers who use them. If you believe your injury was caused by a design or manufacturing error, the attorneys at The Law Offices of Brian Timothy Meyers can help you understand your options. If you were injured because a product failed to include proper warning and safety labels, we can also represent you. Contact our law firm at 888-374-7528 to learn more about our experience seeking justice for clients who were injured by defective products. We are based in Kansas City and we represent clients throughout Missouri and Kansas. Common Dangerous Products Some product liability cases involve appliances, tools or toys with faulty wiring, which causes fires and electrical accidents. Others involve complex medical equipment or other devices, which require substantial research and experts to uncover wrongdoing. Other causes of injury include: • Auto defects • Faulty tires that blowout • Brake defects • Airbag defects • Seat belt failures • Swimming pool accidents • Prescription drugs, including Yasmin and Fentanyl patches • Defective appliances • Dangerous tools and equipment • Medical devices • Children's toys and clothing • Sporting goods and athletic equipment • Recreational vehicles, such as jet skis and ATVs It is important that we begin an investigation of your injury as soon as possible if it was caused by a defective product.
